        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 18 at 1:17AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 117 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles southeast of Chupadera Ranch Airport, or 35 miles south of
Carrizo Springs, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northwestern Webb
County.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
